==Ethnic groups== {{bar box |title=Ethnic groups of Anguilla (2011) <ref name="CIAPAPUANEWGUINEA">{{cite web|url= https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/av.html|title=Central America and Caribbean :: ANGUILLA|publisher= CIA The World Factbook}}</ref> |titlebar=#ddd |left1=Ethnic groups |right1=percent |float=left |bars= {{bar percent|[[Afro-Caribbean|African/black]] |Blue|85.3}} {{bar percent|[[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic]] |Orange| 4.9}} {{bar percent|Mixed|Yellow|3.8}} {{bar percent|[[White people|White]]|Green|3.2}} {{bar percent|Other|Red|1.6}} {{bar percent|[[Indo-Caribbean|East Indian/Indian]]|Orange| 1}} {{bar percent|Unspecified |Purple| 0.3}} }}
==Languages== English (official).
The 2001 census found 11,329 were capable of carrying a conversation in English, and 101 were not. 82 of those spoke Spanish as a first language, 7 spoke Chinese.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://gov.ai/statistics/census/index.htm | title = Anguilla Population & Housing Census | date = 9 May 2001 | publisher = Government of Anguilla}}</ref>
The 2001 census found one heptalingual person, 13 pentalingual people, 35 quadralingual people, 173 trilingual people, 881 bilingual people
The total numbers of speakers of each language were: {| !Language !Speakers |- |English |11,329 |- |Spanish |738 |- |French |342 |- |Chinese |22 |- |Italian |42 |- |German |59 |- |Dutch |95 |- |Other |128 |}
==Religion==
Anguilla is predominantly Christian, with more than 85% identifying themselves with a denomination of Christianity. The major denomination of Christianity in Anguilla as of the 2011 Census Anglicans with 22.7% (down 236). Other large Christian denominations are:
*19.4% Methodist (down 106) *10,5% Pentecostal *8.3% Seventh-Day Adventist (up 261) *7.1% Baptist (up 128) *6.8% Roman Catholic (up 266)
Migration has also resulted in various other religions to make a presence in Anguilla, with 1.3% coming from the following religious groups:
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Religion !! 2001 Census !! 2011 Census |- | [[Rastafarian]] || 85 || 74 |- | [[Hinduism]] || 45 || 58 |- | [[Islam]]|| 36 || 43 |- | [[Judaism]] || 16 || 19 |}
