{{Infobox FBI Ten Most Wanted | name = Fidel Urbina | image = Fidel_Urbina.jpg | image_size = 150px | alt = Photo of Fidel Urbina | caption = | charge = [[Murder (United States law)|First degree murder]], [[kidnapping]], [[Unlawful Flight to Avoid Prosecution]], [[sexual assault]], [[failure to appear]]<ref name=FBI>{{cite web|url=https://www.fbi.gov/wanted/topten/fidel-urbina/view|title=Fidel Urbina|work=United States government|publisher=FBI|accessdate=5 June 2012}}</ref> | reward = [[United States dollar|US]]$100,000 | alias = Lorenzo Maes, Fernando Ramos, Fidel Bahena, Fidel Urbina Aguirre, Lorenzo Fidel, Lorenzo M. Maes, Marcos Antonio, Victor Urbina, "Tonorio"<ref name=FBI /> | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1975|04|24}} | birth_place = [[Mexico]]<ref name=FBI /> | death_date = | death_place = | cause = | nationality = [[Mexico|Mexican]] | race = [[Hispanic]] | gender = Male | height = {{height|ft=5|in=11}} &ndash; {{height|ft=6|in=1}}<ref name=FBI /> | weight = {{convert|165|lb}} &ndash; {{convert|175|lb}}<ref name=AMW>{{cite web|title=Fugitives |url=http://www.amw.com/fugitives/case.cfm?id=60455 |publisher=America's Most Wanted |accessdate=5 June 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121109065420/http://www.amw.com/fugitives/case.cfm?id=60455 |archivedate=9 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> | occupation = [[Auto mechanic]]<ref name=AMW /> | children = | conviction = | conviction_penalty = | conviction_status = | added_date = June 5, 2012<ref name=AMW /> | caught_date = September 22, 2016 | remove_date = | number = 497<ref name=CNN>{{cite news|last=Cratty|first=Carol|title=Alleged murderer and rapist added to FBI's Ten Most Wanted Fugitives list|url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/06/05/justice/fbi-most-wanted-urbina/index.html?hpt=hp_t3|accessdate=5 June 2012|newspaper=CNN|date=5 June 2012}}</ref> | status = Captured }} '''Fidel Urbina''' (born April 24, 1975)<ref name=FBI /> is a Mexican national<ref name=CNN /> former fugitive who was added to the [[FBI Ten Most Wanted Fugitives]] list in June 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/06/06/fidel-urbina-chicago-murd_n_1573997.html|title=Fidel Urbina, Chicago Murder Suspect, Added To FBI's 10 'Most Wanted' List|date=2012-06-06|publisher=Huffington Post}}</ref>
==Background== Urbina is a Mexican national who was working in Chicago as a car mechanic. In March 1998, he allegedly raped a [[Chicago]] waitress in her car and home.<ref name=AMW /> Seven months later—while free on bond—he sexually assaulted and murdered 22-year-old Gabriella Torres, whose body was found in the trunk of a burned-out car in a Chicago alley.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fbi.gov/news/stories/2012/june/urbina_060512/urbina_060512 |title=FBI — New Top Ten Fugitive |publisher=Fbi.gov |date= |accessdate=2012-06-06}}</ref>
==Disappearance== Urbina had been the subject of a manhunt since 1999 despite reported sightings in Mexico. A $100,000 reward was offered for information leading to Urbina's arrest.
Urbina was apprehended September 22, 2016 in Chihuahua, Mexico after 17 years on the run.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fbi.gov/contact-us/field-offices/chicago/news/press-releases/fbi-top-ten-most-wanted-fugitive-fidel-urbina-arrested |title=FBI — FBI Top Ten Most Wanted Fugitive Fidel Urbina Arrested |publisher=Fbi.gov |date=September 23, 2016}}</ref>
