'''Guerret El Anz''' is the time of the year, according to the berber calendar, between February 14 and February 19.
This period is known by its cruel cold.<ref>[http://www.journalistesfaxien.tn/%D9%85%D8%AA%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA/%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B0%D8%A7-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%82%D8%B1%D9%91%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%86%D8%B2/ ماذا تعني “قرّة العنز”؟]</ref>
== Etymology == The word "Guerret" comes from the [[French language|French]] word "guerre" which means "war" in [[English language|English]]. "El Anz" is an [[Arabic]] word which means "[[goats]]".
This expression describe the intense cold during this period like a war endured by the goats who are not very resistant to the cold due to their fine skins.
== History == In [[Tunisia]], it is usual to say "Tjamber Koul w Gamber" ([[Arabic]]: تجمبر كول وقمبر). It is an expression that expresses the need to collect the "oula" and vegetables during "Guerret El Anz".
