The [[British Transplant Society]] awards the '''Medawar Medal''' each year for the best clinical and scientific research presentations by a young scientist or doctor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bts.org.uk/education-training/medawar-medal/|title=Medawar Medal – British Transplantation Society|website=bts.org.uk}}</ref> The award is named after [[Peter Medawar]], a [[Nobel Prize]] winner in Medicine or Physiology.

