{{EngvarB|date=August 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox civilian attack |title=Ogun prison break |partof=[[Prison escape]] |image= Nigeria Ogun State map.png |fatalities = 0 |injuries = at least 1 |type= Prison break |perps=[[prisoner]]s |target= Sagamu minimum Prison |numparts=20 |dfens=4 |date= 4 January 2013 |location=[[Ogun State]], Southwestern [[Nigeria]] }}
The '''Ogun prison break''' was an attack on the Sagamu minimum prison in the southwestern Nigerian city of [[Ogun State]] by the prisoners.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thestreetjournal.org/2013/01/prisoners-subdue-warders-break-jail-in-ogun/|title=Prisoners Subdue Warders, Break Jail in Ogun!|work=THE STREET JOURNAL|accessdate=25 December 2014}}</ref> The attack occurred on 4 January 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nigerianewsday.com/national/1272-prison-break-at-sagamu|title=Prison Break at Sagamu|author=Joseph1|publisher=|accessdate=25 December 2014}}</ref> About 20 prisoners escaped from the prison leaving several prison officials and prisoners seriously injured with no death recorded.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/jail-break-20-inmates-escape-from-sagamu-prison/135394/|title=Jail Break: 20 Inmates Escape from Sagamu Prison, Articles – THISDAY LIVE|publisher=|accessdate=25 December 2014}}</ref> About 4 escaped convicts were rearrested by the Armed Squad of the [[Nigerian Prisons Services|Prison Service]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channelstv.com/2013/01/04/jail-break-20-prisoners-escape-from-sagamu-prison/|title=Jail break: 20 prisoners escape from Sagamu Prison - www.channelstv.com|work=Channels Television|accessdate=25 December 2014}}</ref> It was reported that one escaped convict returned to the prison voluntarily to serve out his short sentence<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/113818-20-prisoners-escape-in-ogun-jailbreak-prison-boss-pledges-discipline.html|title=20 prisoners escape in Ogun jailbreak; prison boss pledges discipline – Premium Times Nigeria|work=Premium Times Nigeria|accessdate=25 December 2014}}</ref>
==Incident== The incident was reported to have occurred on 4 January 2013 at around 3&nbsp;am in the morning.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/20-inmates-escape-in-attempted-jailbreak-at-sagamu-prison/|title=20 inmates escape in attempted jailbreak at Sagamu prison|work=The Punch – Nigeria's Most Widely Read Newspaper|accessdate=25 December 2014}}</ref> Zakari Ibrahim, the Comptroller General of the [[Nigerian Prisons Services]] who confirm the attack claimed that the cause of the prison break was unclear.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.medianigeria.com/11282/20-prisoners-escape-in-sagamu-ogun-state-prison/|title=20 Prisoners Escape in Sagamu, Ogun State Prison|work=Media Nigeria|accessdate=25 December 2014}}</ref> The incident resulted in the remover of Omobitan, the officer-in-charge of the facility from office for negligence of duty.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/sagamu-jailbreak-prisons-sacks-officer-in-charge/|title=Sagamu jailbreak: Prisons sacks officer-in-charge|work=The Punch – Nigeria's Most Widely Read Newspaper|accessdate=25 December 2014}}</ref>
