{{infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = Tzigane | title_orig = | translator = | image = | caption = | author = [[Eleanor Smith (writer)|Eleanor Smith]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[United Kingdom]] | language = English | series = | genre = [[Romance novel|Romance]] | publisher = | release_date = 1935 | english_release_date = | media_type = Print | pages = | isbn = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Tzigane''''' is a novel by the English writer Lady [[Eleanor Smith (writer)|Eleanor Smith]], which was first published in 1935. Along with several of her other works it contains a [[wikt:gypsy|gypsy]] theme.
==Film adaptation== {{Main article|Gypsy (1937 film)}} In 1937 the novel was adapted into a film ''[[Gypsy (1937 film)|Gypsy]]'' directed by [[Roy William Neill]].<ref>Low p.326</ref>
